# BEHAVIOR RULES

## Before writing any code you MUST:
1. Read CursorInstructions\requirement.md fully
2. Confirm all APIs against CursorInstructions\API_List\API.json
3. Confirm all components against scraped_components\
4. Output a short implementation plan:
   - Files to create
   - Files to modify
   - APIs to use (program + transaction)
   - Components to use (Soho IDS)
   - Business logic flow summary
5. Wait for confirmation before proceeding IF in Plan mode
6. Proceed autonomously IF in Agent mode but still output the plan first

## While writing code you MUST:
- Follow every rule in sections 1–14 of this file exactly
- Never deviate from the API call pattern in rule 4
- Never skip the hasError() check
- Never hardcode text — always use Transloco keys
- Never use plain HTML equivalents of Soho IDS components
- Always use ?.trim() on string inputs
- Always wrap API calls in try/catch
- Always show loading state during API calls
- Always handle empty results and error states in the UI

## After writing code you MUST:
- Update src/assets/api.json with any new API calls, sorted A→Z
- Confirm src/assets/parametre.json version is correct
- List all files created or modified
- Flag anything that needs manual attention (e.g. IONAPI config,
  custom API fields that need verification in M3)

---

# PROJECT STRUCTURE RULES
- All M3 API calls → shared service only (e.g. api.service.ts)
- Components → UI only, no direct API calls
- UserContext → initialized via APP_INITIALIZER at bootstrap, never in ngOnInit
- app.component.html → always starts with soho-icons + masthead
- src/assets/api.json → live registry of all APIs used, sorted A→Z
- src/assets/parametre.json → project version and global parameters

---

# API CALL PATTERN — ALWAYS USE THIS EXACT STRUCTURE

async call_[ProgramName]_[TransactionName](param1: string, param2: string): Promise<any> {
  try {
    const inputRecord = new MIRecord();
    inputRecord.setString('FIELD1', param1?.trim());
    inputRecord.setString('FIELD2', param2?.trim());

    const request: IMIRequest = {
      program: 'PROGRAMNAME',
      transaction: 'TRANSACTIONNAME',
      record: inputRecord,
      maxReturnedRecords: 0,
      outputFields: []
    };

    const response: IMIResponse = await this.miService.execute(request).toPromise();

    if (response.hasError()) {
      return [{ error: true, errorMessage: response.errorMessage }];
    }

    return response.items.length > 0 ? response.items : response.items;
  } catch (error: any) {
    console.error("Error:", error);
    return [{ error: true, errorMessage: error.message || error }];
  }
}

