# ASSETS FILES — ALWAYS MAINTAIN BOTH

## src/assets/api.json
- Every API used in the project, sorted A→Z by program then transaction
- Updated every time a new API call is added to the shared service
- Format:
  [
    {
      "program": "CMS100MI",
      "transaction": "LstC04_CUISSOND",
      "description": "List cuisson data",
      "inputs": ["F_RDAT", "T_RDAT", "F_WMST", "T_WMST", "VMFACI"],
      "outputs": []
    }
  ]

## src/assets/parametre.json
- Project version and global parameters
- Version displayed in masthead via {{appVersion.version}}
- Format:
  {
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "appName": "MAH33 Cuisson Pommes",
    "environment": "production"
  }

---

# CUSTOM APIs — SPECIAL HANDLING
- CMS100MI, MDBREADMI, EXT...MI are NOT in CursorInstructions\API_List\API.json
- Their full input/output definition MUST be in requirement.md
- If CursorInstructions\requirement.md does not define a custom API and it is needed — STOP and ask
- Never guess or invent fields for custom APIs

---

# CODING STANDARDS
- TypeScript strict typing always
- Never use 'any' unless absolutely justified
- async/await only — never raw .subscribe() for API calls
- Always unsubscribe on component destroy
- OnPush change detection where possible
- Naming conventions:
  - Components/services: kebab-case filenames
  - Methods: camelCase
  - Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
  - API methods: call_[ProgramName]_[TransactionName]
  - Translation keys: 'componentName.elementDescription'
- Never introduce custom CSS classes that conflict with Soho IDS
- Never hardcode user-facing strings — always use Transloco keys

---

# ERROR HANDLING & UX
- Always show soho-busy-indicator during API calls
- Always disable action buttons while an API call is in progress
- Always show Soho IDS message/toast for API errors
- Never use browser alert()
- Always handle: loading state, empty results, error state
- Never let an API error crash the UI silently

---

# TRANSLATIONS
- Use TranslocoDirective + @jsverse/transloco for all user-facing text
- Translation key format: 'componentName.elementDescription'
  e.g. 'filter.dateFrom', 'grid.noResults', 'button.save'
- Refer to SampleH5SDK for translation file structure

---

# ANGULAR MODULE RULES
- Always import correct Soho modules for components used
- Never import unused modules
- Always refer to SampleH5SDK\C04-Cuisson-Pomme\src\app\app.module.ts
  for correct module structure
- Lazy load feature modules where possible

---

# GIT RULES
- Never commit .ionapi files — always in .gitignore
- Always commit .cursorrules so the whole team shares the same rules
- Always commit src/assets/api.json and src/assets/parametre.json
- Bump version in parametre.json on every release

---

# PROMPT ENGINEERING — HOW TO PROMPT ME CORRECTLY

## Good prompt format — always use this structure:

  CONTEXT:
  [What screen or feature you are building]

  TASK:
  [What exactly needs to be implemented]

  APIs:
  [M3 program + transaction, or "refer to requirement.md"]

  COMPONENTS:
  [Expected Soho IDS components in the UI]

  BUSINESS LOGIC:
  [Step by step flow]

  CUSTOM APIs (if any):
  [Full input/output for CMS100MI, MDBREADMI, EXT...MI]

  REFERENCE:
  [SampleH5SDK project or specific file if relevant]

## Agent mode — use when:
- Requirement is fully defined
- All APIs are standard and verified in api.json
- Small to medium feature (1–3 components)
- You want full end-to-end implementation in one go

## Plan mode — use when:
- Feature is complex or multi-step
- Involves custom APIs needing careful handling
- You want to approve each step before proceeding
- First time implementing a new component type or flow
- Debugging — you want to go step by step

## How to correct me mid-session:
- Be specific: "the API call is missing mandatory field WHLO, add it"
- Reference the rule: "this breaks rule 4 — follow the exact API call pattern"
- If fully off track: "reset — re-read .cursorrules and requirement.md
  and give me the plan again"

## Starting a new chat session:
Always begin with:
"Read .cursorrules and CursorInstructions\requirement.md before we start.
 Confirm you have read both before proceeding."

## Context window warning:
- I do NOT remember previous chat sessions
- If the conversation gets long and I start losing context — start a new chat
- Break large features into smaller focused prompts per component or service method

## Bad prompts — never do these:
- "Build the whole app" — too vague
- "Add a grid" — which data? which API? which columns?
- "Fix it" — what is broken? what is expected?
- "Make it look nice" — Soho IDS handles styling
- Any prompt with no API definition for custom APIs — I will guess and be wrong

## Good prompts — always include:
- Specific task with clear scope
- API program + transaction explicitly named
- Expected Soho IDS components listed
- Business flow described step by step
- Edge cases: empty results, errors, loading states
- Reference to SampleH5SDK if a similar pattern exists

